22 SUMMARY
2233 This bill authorizes the Department of Public Safety, Gambling Control Unit to issue
2244 licenses to operate electronic lucky seven devices to eligible organizations. The bill
2255 provides restrictions on the number, location and operation of electronic lucky seven
2266 devices and requires licensees to operate at least one kiosk for the redemption of electronic
2277 lucky seven vouchers. It also requires distributors of electronic lucky seven devices to be
2288 licensed. The bill also makes other necessary changes to the charitable gaming laws.
